frameDefinitions: This frame is concerned with nouns denoting a part or parts of a Whole entity .
An event or state (here termed an Eventuality) or time-Period is described in terms of the Degree to which its duration diverges from a standard.
A Speaker communicates a message stating an Item's membership in a Category, i.e., asserts that the Item has the defining characteristics of the Category.
A person (Speaker) expresses a Message or mental content, broadly understood, in a particular Manner.
Criteria exist that identify a particular Subset of a Group of things into members and non-members.
A physical object, the Artifact, is produced by a Creator to stimulate the perceptions, emotions, or cognition of an audience.
frameExamples: Kim forgot a large <t><fex name='Part'>part</fex></t> of the story.
After a <t>lengthy</t> discussion with the Foreign Minister, Mr. Qian Qichen, they met the Prime Minister.
He <t>depicted</t> his involvement as merely peripheral.
Urban areas have> a higher teen suicide <t><fex name='Ratio'>rate</fex></t> than rural areas.
Sir Denis Mahon is the owner of the most important private collection of Italian Baroque <t><fex name='Artifact'>paintings</fex></t>.
listRoleDefinitions: An undivided entity having all its <fen>Part</fen>s.

A situation, action or event whose duration is being described.  The Eventuality occurs as the External Argument if the adjective is used predicatively, or as the modified noun if the adjective is used attributively: <fex name='Eventuality'>The lecture</fex> was <t>short</t>. We had a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Eventuality'>conversation</fex>.

Sometimes these adjectives describe simply a period of time, rather than an event or state.  The Period almost invariably occurs as the modified noun with an attributive adjective: We waited for only a <t>short</t> <fex name='Period'>time</fex>. Use of the drug over a <t>lengthy</t> <fex name='Period'>period</fex> can cause memory loss.
The individual that communicates the message concerning the <fen>Category</fen> of an <fen>Item</fen>.
The class of entities with characteristics that match those of the <fen>Item</fen> according to the portrayal of the <fen>Speaker</fen>.
The entity that the <fen>Speaker</fen> portrays as belonging to a <fen>Category</fen>.
The piece of text in which a <fen>Speaker</fen> communicates their categorization of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The point in time at which the <fen>Speaker</fen> makes a characterization of the <fen>Item</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Speaker</fen> characterizes the <fen>Item</fen>
<fen>Speaker</fen>, the person who encodes the <fen>Message</fen>, occurs as the External Argument of all the verbs:
The <fen>Message</fen> is almost invariably expressed in an NP Object. (The only exceptions occur with the verb <t>express</t>, which is occasionally used with that-clause complements.)

For most of the words in this frame, some expression of <fen>Manner</fen> or <fen>Medium</fen> is obligatory. As in other frames, <fen>Manner</fen> expressions characterize the action (in this case, the speech act performed by the <fen>Speaker</fen>). However, a wide range of <fen>Manner</fen> expressions occurs in this frame, including the following types:
<fen>Medium</fen> expresses the <fen>Medium</fen> of communication, such as the language used or the specific type of text in which the <fen>Message</fen> occurs:
A representation of the conditions upon which membership to a <fen>Subset</fen> of a <fen>Group</fen> is determined.
The members of a <fen>Group</fen> that fulfill particular <fen>Criteria</fen> to belong to a <fen>Subset</fen> of the <fen>Group</fen>.
The numerical representation of the size of the <fen>Subset</fen> relative to the size of the <fen>Group</fen>.
This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Artifact</fen> is presently located.

Sergey had  half <fex>of the pizza</fex> for breakfast.
However, <fex>'A Brief History of Medicine'</fex> characterizes influenza as the most deadly plague, overall.
The Prime Minister expressed <fex>her sympathy for the victims</fex>.
True Manner: You should phrase it <fex>carefully</fex>.

California has a high <fex>divorce</fex> rate compared to other states.
New laws have raised crime rates <fex>by 5%</fex>
